The paper discusses a new algorithm for learning correlations between two datasets, which can be used for statistical inference and supervised learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to machine learning and data analysis. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CV (Computer Vision) are likely candidates given the focus on learning algorithms and feature maps. Additionally, cs.ST (Statistics) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are also possible categories given the emphasis on statistical inference and information metrics.
